eecalcs.conductors

Class CondProp

  • java.lang.Object
    • eecalcs.conductors.CondProp

  • public class CondProp
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates static data and methods about properties of conductors as defined in NEC 2014 tables 310.15(B)(16), 8, 9, 5 and 5A.

        public static PropertySet bySize(java.lang.String size)
        Returns a PropertySet object for the given conductor size. If the size of the conductor is not valid, an invalidPropertySet object is returned.
        Parameters:
        size - The size of the conductor
        Returns:
        A PropertySet object.
        See Also:
        getInvalidPropertySet()

      • getInsulatedAreaIn2

        protected static double getInsulatedAreaIn2(java.lang.String conductorSize,
                                            java.lang.String insulationName)
        Returns the area in square inches of an insulated conductor (conductor and insulation altogether) of size conductorSize and of insulation insulationName.
        Parameters:
        conductorSize - The size of the conductor as defined by Size
        insulationName - The insulation type of the conductor as defined by Insul
        Returns:
        The area of the insulated conductor or zero if any of the parameter is invalid.

      • compareSizes

        public static int compareSizes(java.lang.String sizeLeft,
                               java.lang.String sizeRight)
        Compares two conductor sizes. This methods does not check for validity of the conductor sizes. If one of the conductor is invalid the result will not make any sense.
        Parameters:
        sizeLeft - The size of the left side conductor to be compared as defined by Size
        sizeRight - The size of the right side conductor to be compared as defined by Size
        Returns:
        -1 if sizeLeft is smaller than sizeRight, 0 if both are the same size of 1 if sizeLeft is bigger than sizeRight

      • getSizes

        public static java.lang.String[] getSizes()
        Returns:
        Return a table containing all the conductor sizes as defined defined by Size

      • getFullSizeName

        protected static java.lang.String getFullSizeName(java.lang.String size)
        Returns the full size name of the given conductor size.
        Parameters:
        size - The size of the conductor as defined by Size
        Returns:
        The full size name including the prefix for AWG or KCMIL. If the size is not valid an empty string is returned.

      • getInvalidPropertySet

        public static PropertySet getInvalidPropertySet()
        Returns the invalidPropertySet object. An invalidPropertySet object is a particular PropertySet object that contains only zeroes for all the properties of the a conductor. The size of the conductor returned by an invalidPropertySet object is "Not assigned!".
        Returns:
        The invalidPropertySet object.
        See Also:
        PropertySet
